dismissalText.commentary: BJ Watling lbw b Rampaul 60 (98b 5x4 0x6 138m) SR: 61.22

dismissalComment.html: referral, a big appeal for lbw is upheld, Watling argues for a review again, that looked plumb and it is plumb, it was a length ball and he looked to thump that towards midwicket, he missed and was struck low on the pads in front of middle, it was the end of the innings, and only No. 11 to come, so Watling decided to punt on the review, doesn't work this time though, he's a goner, end of a important knock for Watling, with several other keepers looking for a place in the NZ side

talk about immediate impact! length ball jags away and Guptill pokes at it outside off without moving his feet, gets the outside edge and through to Sammy at second slip, taken low and to his right, Guptill is gone for 1

headshotImage.caption: Daniel Flynn player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Daniel Flynn player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: oh dear! just after that audacious shot, Flynn looks to crash a length ball through the covers, inside-edges on to the stumps, perhaps that ball moved in a touch and Flynn didn't adjust for that, his wait for an ODI half-century continues, that average does not make good reading, Russell gets his second wicket

headshotImage.caption: Rob Nicol player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Rob Nicol player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: another down for New Zealand, and another for Russell, Nicol so far has chosen which ball to hit judiciously, this time he charges down the track and though it is a short ball, he looks to power it towards midwicket, top edges towards deep square leg, the fielder awaits, and the fears about New Zealand's batting are being realised

and he takes his fourth off the final delivery of his quota, not the best of deliveries, it was full and sliding down the leg side, whipped towards short fine leg for a catch, a few yards either side of that fielder and that was four

dismissalComment.html: Simmons is gone, New Zealand have struck early, that was slanting down the leg side, tickled through to the keeper, who does well to get to his left to catch that, Simmons starts to walk away as he knows he has edged that, the on-field umpire wanted to check for a no-ball, replay suggested Mills had overstepped, I was expecting Simmons to be called back, instead he is sent on his way

batsmen.shot: off side drive on front foot

headshotImage.caption: Sunil Narine player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Sunil Narine player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: this time he does, and he sends that to the deep point boundary, a full and wide ball, an utterly one-sided game this, would have been a travesty if New Zealand escaped because of the rain

commentPostTextItems.html: That was pretty much a perfect game for West Indies, starting with the new ball spell of Andre Russell, backed up by the bewitching bowling of Sunil Narine, who proved far too tricky for the inexperieced New Zealand batting. BJ Watling's half-century helped New Zealand avoid complete humiliation, but the 190 they put up was never likely to test the home side, even less so when NZ lost Ellis to an injury reducing their bowling options. Gayle got his third successive half-century, and Smith reached a fifty of his own to ensure there were no troubles in the chase. A lengthy rain delay kept the home crowd waiting but once the showers went away and play resumed, it was a quick finish.
Abhishek Purohit is putting the finishing touches to his match report, check it out.

Kane Williamson: "I guess we didn't start too well with the bat, we scrapped our way to some sort of the total, and again the power-hitters hurt us. We can learn from the West Indies, they bowled well, swung it a bit, we need to learn from the mistakes we are making. We are looking to improve and close the gap, which is looking quite big at the moment. We are a young side, playing a very experienced side, we have to show the West Indies side that we can compete."
Darren Sammy: "Very pleasing (Russell's performance). For a long time we have been struggling with the bat, and it is nice to see us winning by nine wickets."

Man of the Match is Andre Russell: "I knew how important this game was. It was my mom's birthday, I gave her a good surprise. The wicket tends to have some moisture in the morning, we had to keep it tight then as it gets a little flat in the middle overs."
Well, that's about a wrap from us here. Catch you during the second game on Saturday. Seeya!

commentPreTextItems.html: Guptill, of all people, bowling now

commentTextItems.html: well outside off, smith wanted to send that out of the ground, doesn't connect
works it away towards short midwicket for a single, that was a full ball well outside off stump, Smith mistimes his drive

headshotImage.caption: Jacob Oram player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Jacob Oram player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: angling down the leg side, helped to the right of the keeper, who moves quickly across and takes off a glove and underarms the ball towards the stumps
again on the pads, again Smith clips it, just a single this time as the deep square leg fielder stops it
another boundary, West Indies finishing this in a hurry, that was a full ball on the pads, whipped to the deep backward square leg boundary for four
a slower one from Oram, helped towards deep square leg for a single
Oram continues the trend of full tosses, slightly high this one, just above the knee roll and that is turned towards square leg

commentPostTextItems.html: Rokhan: "What's the bet despite a thrashing in this series , NZ still overperforms in the world t20 and WI underperform? :P"

commentTextItems.html: thumps it towards a wide mid-on, it is a full toss again from Southee, a single is taken

headshotImage.caption: Jacob Oram player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Jacob Oram player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: on the pads, clipped towards deep midwicket, that was another full toss from Southee
a yorker on middle stump, squeezed out towards extra cover
a low full toss well outside off, slashed away to the sweeper cover boundary, some of the fans in the crowd also join in signalling the boundary

dropped by Nicol, smith skied that overpitched ball towards point, several fielders were converging on that, Nicol called for it, got under it in time, tried to take it with his fingers pointing up with the ball coming over his shoulder, couldn't hang on
another full one, outside off, that is drilled towards long-on for a single

headshotImage.caption: Jacob Oram player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Jacob Oram player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: short ball after those two full ones, that one rears sharply outside off, Smith watches it and swerves out of the line
Smith mistimes it as he pushes another full delivery back towards the bowler
Oram around the wicket, a full ball is pushed back down the track
driven with brutal power towards long-off, Nathan McCullum cuts that off at long-off, it was a length ball outside off
full and very wide outside off, wide

dismissalComment.html: talk about immediate impact! length ball jags away and Guptill pokes at it outside off without moving his feet, gets the outside edge and through to Sammy at second slip, taken low and to his right, Guptill is gone for 1

headshotImage.caption: Daniel Flynn player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Daniel Flynn player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Daniel Flynn player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Daniel Flynn player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Daniel Flynn b Russell 12 (16b 2x4 0x6 28m) SR: 75

dismissalComment.html: oh dear! just after that audacious shot, Flynn looks to crash a length ball through the covers, inside-edges on to the stumps, perhaps that ball moved in a touch and Flynn didn't adjust for that, his wait for an ODI half-century continues, that average does not make good reading, Russell gets his second wicket

headshotImage.caption: Rob Nicol player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Rob Nicol player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Rob Nicol player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Rob Nicol player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Rob Nicol c Simmons b Russell 14 (26b 2x4 0x6 43m) SR: 53.84

dismissalComment.html: another down for New Zealand, and another for Russell, Nicol so far has chosen which ball to hit judiciously, this time he charges down the track and though it is a short ball, he looks to power it towards midwicket, top edges towards deep square leg, the fielder awaits, and the fears about New Zealand's batting are being realised

headshotImage.caption: Dean Brownlie player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Dean Brownlie player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Dean Brownlie player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Dean Brownlie player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Sunil Narine player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Sunil Narine player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Dean Brownlie lbw b Narine 1 (13b 0x4 0x6 22m) SR: 7.69

dismissalComment.html: and Brownlie fails the Narine test, he never looked like passing it, he looked to play that straighter one from the crease, he misses, struck on the pads in front of middle, doesn't take long for the umpire to lift the finger, New Zealand four down, this isn't looking good for them

dismissalText.commentary: Kane Williamson c Ramdin b Sammy 24 (52b 1x4 0x6 67m) SR: 46.15

dismissalComment.html: Sammy gets rid of his opposing number, New Zealand have lost their fifth, KW was looking to run that down to third man, opens the face to a gentle straight back of a length delivery, ends up feathering it through to the keeper, disappointing stroke that

headshotImage.longCaption: Ravi Rampaul player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Jacob Oram b Rampaul 32 (39b 2x4 2x6 42m) SR: 82.05

dismissalComment.html: slightly slower from Rampaul, 123kph, Oram looking to send that into orbit, that sneaks under his bat, and past the back pad to crash into leg stump, end of a fighting stand

headshotImage.longCaption: Andrew Ellis player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.longCaption: Andrew Ellis player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.longCaption: Sunil Narine player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Andrew Ellis b Narine 14 (27b 0x4 0x6 44m) SR: 51.85

dismissalComment.html: Narine strikes on his second delivery, once more Ellis moves a bit away from leg stump, not the dramatic step away but a more small one, it was an offspinner from Narine, Ellis looked to cut that, he misses and the ball hit the top of middle

dismissalText.commentary: Kyle Mills c Samuels b Russell 1 (7b 0x4 0x6 7m) SR: 14.28

dismissalComment.html: and he takes his fourth off the final delivery of his quota, not the best of deliveries, it was full and sliding down the leg side, whipped towards short fine leg for a catch, a few yards either side of that fielder and that was four

headshotImage.caption: BJ Watling player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: BJ Watling player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.longCaption: BJ Watling player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Ravi Rampaul player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ravi Rampaul player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: BJ Watling lbw b Rampaul 60 (98b 5x4 0x6 138m) SR: 61.22

dismissalComment.html: referral, a big appeal for lbw is upheld, Watling argues for a review again, that looked plumb and it is plumb, it was a length ball and he looked to thump that towards midwicket, he missed and was struck low on the pads in front of middle, it was the end of the innings, and only No. 11 to come, so Watling decided to punt on the review, doesn't work this time though, he's a goner, end of a important knock for Watling, with several other keepers looking for a place in the NZ side

headshotImage.caption: BJ Watling player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: BJ Watling player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Lendl Simmons c Watling b Mills 0 (12b 0x4 0x6 11m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: Simmons is gone, New Zealand have struck early, that was slanting down the leg side, tickled through to the keeper, who does well to get to his left to catch that, Simmons starts to walk away as he knows he has edged that, the on-field umpire wanted to check for a no-ball, replay suggested Mills had overstepped, I was expecting Simmons to be called back, instead he is sent on his way

dismissalText.commentary: Chris Gayle not out 63 (57b 4x4 5x6 104m) SR: 110.52
Dwayne Smith not out 65 (77b 6x4 3x6 93m) SR: 84.41
